pageContext.claim:
“If we would have told you during the campaign that we would create 3.3 million jobs in this short time, everybody back there, the fake news media -- look at all of them.

They're fake news. Everybody back there would have said, can you imagine he's saying we're going to create 3.3 million -- can you believe it? We would have been -- but you know what? We understand. We understand.”
pageContext.analysis: The rate of job growth under Trump is slower than under Obama at the end of his term, so these numbers are not surprising.
